Completing the name of the non-live `beta` repo makes the new-session row
selectable again, because there is no exact live session named `beta`.

    :k C-u beta
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: beta
  1/6 | [C-r] repo: none
   beta                                                                                                                ┃
▌  beta                                     beta                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  beta commit
◆





```

